From: conda-forge recipe maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] Strip CLI-tool Requires-Dist entries for conda-forge

Upstream lists `uv` and `git-annex` as `Requires-Dist` so that
`pip install xorq` bootstraps both CLI tools from PyPI. On conda-forge
they are packaged separately as native binaries (Rust and Haskell
respectively) and do not ship a Python `.dist-info/` directory, which
makes `pip check` report them as missing even though `$PREFIX/bin/uv`
and `$PREFIX/bin/git-annex` are present. Both are still declared in
the recipe's `run:` block, so the conda solver still pulls them in.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -54,10 +54,8 @@
     "prometheus-client>=0.22.1",
     "cryptography>=45.0.3",
     "strenum>=0.4.15 ; python_version <= '3.10'",
-    "uv>=0.7.20",
     "rich>=13.9.4",
     "click>=8.0",
-    "git-annex>=10.20250220",
     "gitpython>=3.1.46",
     "textual>=1.0.0",
     "filelock>=3.13",
